Bungoma Governor Wycliffe Wangamati has asked Sirisia MP John Waluke to support his administration. The tendency of the MP to work in isolation will derail development to his constituency, he said Speaking in Kimabole village during a thanksgiving ceremony Public Administration executive Richard Sabwami,Wangamati said Sirisia has many problems which can be solved through partnership. Sirisia faces water shortage problem and its education standards have started deteriorating. Wangamati said his administration cannot solve the problems single handedly. Waluke is nursing governor ambitions in 2022, but he should first support the current team, the governor said. Wangamati said he is ready to work with all elected leaders. Sabwami thanked the governor for appointing him.